text: :For another species commonly known as the masked tree frog, see Smilisca phaeota. The masked tree frog (Smilisca manisorum) is a frog that lives in Costa Rica, Panama, Honduras and Nicaragua. It lives in forests near the ocean. Scientists have seen it as high as 540 meters above sea level. ==References== Category:Frogs of North America
title: Smilisca manisorum
